<item>
            <title>[SOLR-9161] SolrPluginUtils.invokeSetters should accommodate setter variants</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-9161</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The code currently assumes that there is only one setter (or if there are several setters then the first one found is used and it could mismatch on the arg type).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Context and motivation is that a class with a&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;void setAFloat(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;float&lt;/span&gt; val) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.val = val;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;setter may wish to also provide a&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;void setAFloat(&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; val) {
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.val = &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Float&lt;/span&gt;.parseFloat(val);
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;convenience setter.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
